Here is the safe read partially delivered.
The remaining logic that needs to be implemented is as follows..
- First it needs to check whether a user belongs to any group
   - if true it renders the group(s) list
   - else it returns a message informing the user that he didn't belong to any group
- When view messages button was clicked, it will query the Graph API using his id, accessToken, and groupId
- The returned data will be used to query the hate speech sentiment endpoint.
- It will analyze the messages and returns the hate speech-free messages
